The student applies the basic knowledge and practical skills related to the business model and plan preparation, product and service development, and company launch. Their short-term and long-term goals are agreed upon with the team, and the necessary activities are mapped out, which are evaluated in a monthly conversation (four conversations in total). The subject ends with introducing ideas and presenting the further action plan to the committeeObjectives/eesmärkid:  Students put into practice their basic knowledge and practical skills for designing, starting, developing and leading business plans and projects.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has passed the subject: - is able to set short- and long-term goals and knows how to achieve them; - can manage the team, himself, and development activities related to the business idea; - knows how to define and analyze problems, set strategic goals, and implement them; - can find and analyze important background information for his business model/business plan draft - knows the principles of intellectual property and can assess the need for intellectual property protection; - have tested their business idea or prototype on potential customers; -has developed his presentation skills and prepared a sales pitch.
